<div id="review_2354366379" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2354366379" />
    <a title="Vikas Singh" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23007922-vikas-singh"><img alt="Vikas Singh" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1591592210p2/23007922.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2354366379?book_show_action=true">Apr 08, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Vikas Singh" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Vikas Singh" href="/user/show/23007922-vikas-singh">Vikas Singh</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/12087370-the-pale-horse">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/23007922-vikas-singh?shelf=owned-book">owned-book</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2354366379" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3659942577493324161">Christie at her poisonous best. What sets apart this novel from her other writings is the development of the plot is not linear. There are interesting diversions to keep you glued till end with great deal of occult and witches in the plot. The inspiration for solving the murder appears to be too sudden. Mrs. Oliver without her friend Poirot manages to add that extra bit of fun and frolic.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


