        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2103891948" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7855503342633683775">I was quite happy with this one. At first I thought it might be dated. Written in 1962, she writes about hip, rich, young girls playing at being poor. I was afraid it was going to be full of silly 60&apos;s lingo, man. You dig? But it wasn&apos;t. <br/><br/>I like that Christie never takes herself too seriously. One of her characters was an author of mysteries, who was having writer&apos;s block. She and the protag, Mark, talked about the three witches in Macbeth and how they should be portrayed as regular women, not so</span>
  <span id="freeText7855503342633683775" style="display:none">I was quite happy with this one. At first I thought it might be dated. Written in 1962, she writes about hip, rich, young girls playing at being poor. I was afraid it was going to be full of silly 60's lingo, man. You dig? But it wasn't. <br /><br />I like that Christie never takes herself too seriously. One of her characters was an author of mysteries, who was having writer's block. She and the protag, Mark, talked about the three witches in Macbeth and how they should be portrayed as regular women, not so over-the-top ugly cackling witches. Christie goes on to introduce three women, all pretty average, who have a reputation in their small village as witches. <br /> <br /><br />I was very happy with the whole murder scenario. Very clever. I figured it out before the characters, but not much before.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="7855503342633683775" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


